$ Graphviz attribute type: color
@ color

The → tools/Graphviz/attributes/types[attribute type] `color` can be applied to the following → tools/Graphviz/attributes[attributes]:
table { llll
                   ☰ → tools/Graphviz/node ☰ → tools/Graphviz/edge ☰ → tools/Graphviz/graph ☰ → tools/Graphviz/cluster ☰
   `bgcolor`       ☰                       ☰                       ☰ ✓                      ☰ ✓                        ☰
   `color`         ☰ ✓                     ☰ ✓                     ☰                        ☰ ✓                        ☰
   `fillcolor`     ☰ ✓                     ☰ ✓                     ☰                        ☰ ✓                        ☰ requires also the `filled` → tools/Graphviz/attributes/style[style] to be set
   `fontcolor`     ☰ ✓                     ☰ ✓                     ☰ ✓                      ☰ ✓                        ☰
   `labelfontcolor`☰ ✓                     ☰                       ☰                        ☰                          ☰
   `pencolor`      ☰                       ☰                       ☰                        ☰ ✓                        ☰
table }

The value of color can be
  • `#rrggbb`
  • `#rrggbbaa`
  • A → tools/Graphviz/attributes/colorscheme/color-name (which is interpreted according to the → tools/Graphviz/attributes/colorscheme/color-scheme-namespace context)


